# User Manual - fatp-drone GUI

![fatp-drone GUI](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> **What is this thing?** A browser-based ground control station for a drone running real compiled C++ via WebAssembly (WASM). Everything you click triggers actual C++ logic, not JavaScript mocks. The bottom-right corner always shows `CommandParser::execute()  real C++` to confirm this.

---

## Layout Overview

The UI is split into four zones:

| Zone | Where | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| **Left Sidebar** | Far left column | Subsystem toggles & arm checklist |
| **Main Panel** | Center | Feature graph + flight mode pipeline + console |
| **Right Sidebar** | Far right column | Quick actions & live telemetry |
| **Status Bar** | Very bottom | WASM/armed/airborne state indicators |

---

## Top Navigation Bar

```
[fatp-drone]  REAL WASM  FAT-P ECOSYSTEM          [REAL C++  WASM]  [PREFLIGHT]
```

- **fatp-drone**  app logo/home, does nothing dramatic
- **REAL C++  WASM** (green pill, top-right)  confirms the C++ backend compiled with clang/wasm32 is loaded and running. If this is missing or red, your WASM build failed.
- **PREFLIGHT** (teal button, top-right)  jumps you back to the Preflight stage from wherever you are in the pipeline

---

## Flight Stage Pipeline (top of main panel)

```
[PREFLIGHT]  [ARMED]  [FLYING]  [LANDING]  [EMERGENCY]
```

These are the five states your drone moves through. The currently active stage is highlighted. You cannot skip stages arbitrarily  the system enforces prerequisites.

| Stage | What it means |
|-------|--------------|
| **PREFLIGHT** | On the ground, checking systems. Nothing can fly yet. |
| **ARMED** | Motors are enabled and ready. Propellers can spin  stay clear. |
| **FLYING** | Vehicle is airborne and under active control. |
| **LANDING** | Descent sequence initiated. |
| **EMERGENCY** | Something went wrong. Motors may cut. See Emergency section below. |

The red " need 6 more" message under PREFLIGHT means 6 arm requirements still aren't met  you can't arm until those are green.

---

## Left Sidebar

### ARM CHECKLIST

Six items must all be  green before you can arm:

| Item | What it checks |
|------|---------------|
| **IMU** | Inertial Measurement Unit  accelerometer/gyro online |
| **Barometer** | Altitude sensor online |
| **BatteryMonitor** | Battery reporting valid voltage |
| **ESC** | Electronic Speed Controllers responding |
| **MotorMix** | Motor output mixer configured |
| **RCReceiver** | Radio control link established |

Red dot = not ready. Enable the corresponding toggle in the Sensors/Power/Communications sections below to fix it.

---

### FLIGHT MODE

Six flight mode buttons let you switch how the drone controls itself:

| Mode | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| **Manual** | Raw stick input goes straight to motors. You fly it. No assists. |
| **Stabilize** | Auto-levels the craft, but you control throttle/direction. |
| **AltHold** | Holds altitude automatically; you steer. |
| **PosHold** | Holds position (GPS) and altitude. Hands-off hover. |
| **Auto** | Follows a pre-programmed mission. |
| **RTL** | Return To Launch  flies home and lands automatically. |

---

### SENSORS / POWER / COMMUNICATIONS / SAFETY (toggle lists)

Each subsystem has a toggle switch (the pill on the right). **Blue/on = active. Grey/off = disabled.**

**Sensors:**
- IMU, GPS, Barometer, Compass, OpticalFlow, Lidar

**Power:**
- BatteryMonitor, ESC, MotorMix

**Communications:**
- RCReceiver, Telemetry, Datalink

**Safety:**
- Geofence, Failsafe, CollisionAvoid, EmergencyStop

Toggling these on/off is how you satisfy the ARM CHECKLIST. The system maps directly  e.g., turning on IMU here lights up the IMU arm checklist item.

---

## Main Panel  Feature Graph

The big dark graph in the center shows the **live dependency map** of all features. Nodes glow when active. Lines show relationships:

| Line color/style | Meaning |
|-----------------|---------|
| ** REQUIRES** (teal solid) | This feature won't work without that one |
| ** IMPLIES** (teal dashed) | Enabling this auto-enables that |
| **== EXCLUDES** (red dashed) | These two features can't be active together |
| **~~ PREEMPTS** (orange) | This feature overrides/suspends that one |

**Feature groups visible in the graph:**

- **FLIGHTMODES** box  AltHold, Autonomous, Manual, PosHold, RTL, Stabilize
- **SENSORS** box  Barometer, Compass, GPS, IMU, Lidar, OpticalFlow
- **POWER** box  BatteryMon, ESC, MotorMix
- **COMMS** box  Datalink, RCReceiver, Telemetry
- **SAFETY** box  CollisionAvoid, EmergencyStop, Failsafe, Geofence

> **Tip:** Click any node in the graph to toggle it. Recent command paths flash along the edges so you can see what triggered what.

The label above the graph  **Live  FeatureManager JSON**  means the graph is reflecting the real-time state of the C++ FeatureManager object. Click **JSON** (right sidebar) to dump the raw state.

---

## Console / Log Area (bottom of main panel)

The dark terminal area shows timestamped output from the C++ backend:

```
16:19:17 | fatp-drone  Real WASM Build
16:19:17 | C++ compiled with clang-10 wasm32
16:19:17   CommandParser::execute() running real compiled C++.
16:19:17   Fat-P FeatureManager, StateMachine, Signal, TelemetryLog active.
16:19:17   HINT: Arm requires: IMU, Barometer, BatteryMonitor, ESC, MotorMix, RCReceiver
```

- Highlighted lines (bright) = most recent commands
- `HINT:` lines = the system telling you exactly what's blocking you

**Command input:**
```
[Preflight] >  type command or click buttons         [EXEC]
```
You can type raw commands here and hit **EXEC**, or just use the buttons  they submit the same commands under the hood.

---

## Right Sidebar  Quick Actions

| Button | What it does |
|--------|-------------|
| **ARM** | Arms the drone (enables motors). All 6 checklist items must be green first. |
| **DISARM** | Immediately disarms. Motors stop. Safe to approach. |
| **TAKEOFF** | Commands an automated takeoff to a default altitude. Drone must be armed. |
| **LAND** | Initiates a controlled descent and landing at current position. |
| **LANDING COMPLETE** | Confirms the drone has touched down (may need manual confirmation). |
| **STATUS** | Dumps current system status to the console log. |
| **LOG** | Opens/shows the full telemetry log. |
| **JSON** | Prints the raw FeatureManager JSON state to console  useful for debugging. |
| **EMERGENCY STOP** | **Cuts all motors immediately.** Use only if the drone is about to do something dangerous. This will cause it to drop. |
| **RESET FROM EMERGENCY** | Clears the emergency state so you can restart the preflight sequence. |

---

## Right Sidebar  Telemetry Live

Real-time readouts from the vehicle:

| Field | What it shows |
|-------|--------------|
| **VEHICLE STATE** | Current flight stage (Preflight, Armed, Flying, etc.) |
| **ENABLED SUBSYS** | Bitmask or count of active subsystems |
| **FLIGHT MODE** | Active flight mode (Manual, Stabilize, etc.) |
| **ARM READY** | YES/NO  are all arm requirements met? |
| **IMU** | ON/OFF |
| **GPS** | ON/OFF |
| **BATTERY** | ON/OFF |
| **ESC** | ON/OFF |
| **RC RECEIVER** | ON/OFF |

---

## Status Bar (very bottom)

```
 WASM ACTIVE     ARMED     AIRBORNE
```

Three indicator dots at the bottom-left:
- **WASM ACTIVE**  the C++ WASM module is loaded and running
- **ARMED**  vehicle is currently armed
- **AIRBORNE**  vehicle is currently flying

Bottom-right confirms the exact build: `CommandParser::execute()  real C++  clang-10 wasm32-wasi`

---

## Typical Workflow (start to flight)

1. **Load the app**  confirm WASM ACTIVE dot is green and "REAL C++  WASM" pill is lit
2. **Enable subsystem toggles**  turn on IMU, Barometer, BatteryMonitor, ESC, MotorMix, RCReceiver in the left sidebar
3. **Watch ARM CHECKLIST**  all 6 items should turn green; "need X more" counter should reach 0
4. **Select a flight mode**  start with Stabilize or AltHold if you're learning
5. **Click ARM**  vehicle arms, ARMED indicator lights up
6. **Click TAKEOFF**  vehicle lifts off, AIRBORNE lights up, pipeline moves to FLYING
7. **Fly**  use flight mode buttons to switch modes as needed
8. **Click LAND**  vehicle descends
9. **Click LANDING COMPLETE**  confirm touchdown
10. **Click DISARM**  safe to approach

---

## Emergency Procedures

- **EMERGENCY STOP**  instant motor cutoff. The drone will fall. Use only on the ground or if a crash is preferable to the alternative.
- After emergency stop, the pipeline moves to **EMERGENCY** stage (red).
- Click **RESET FROM EMERGENCY** to clear the fault and return to PREFLIGHT.
- The **Failsafe** and **CollisionAvoid** subsystems can trigger emergency states automatically  make sure those toggles are on during normal operation.
